            Replay a JSONL trace file. Tool results are read from the trace — no live tool execution occurs. Useful for deterministic testing and debugging.
          </p>
          <div class="rounded-xl p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-7" style="background: var(--c-code); border: 1px solid var(--c-b); color: var(--c-t3);">
            <div><span style="color: var(--c-emerald);">halcon replay</span> &lt;trace-path&gt;               Replay a trace file (reads tool results from file)</div>
            <div class="mt-2" style="color: var(--c-t4);"># Tip: create a trace with --trace-out, then replay with halcon replay</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- halcon metrics -->
        <div id="metrics" class="mb-10 scroll-mt-24">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-1 font-mono" style="color: var(--c-p);">halcon metrics</h3>
