          <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--c-t3);">
            Start Halcón as an MCP server over stdio. Exposes all 21 tools via JSON-RPC to any MCP-compatible IDE (Cursor, VS Code, Zed, etc.).
          </p>
          <div class="rounded-xl p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-7" style="background: var(--c-code); border: 1px solid var(--c-b); color: var(--c-t3);">
            <div><span style="color: var(--c-emerald);">halcon mcp-server</span> [--working-dir &lt;path&gt;]  Start MCP server on stdio</div>
            <div class="mt-2" style="color: var(--c-t4);"># Add to your .mcp.json:</div>
            <div>{`{ "mcpServers": { "halcon": { "command": "halcon", "args": ["mcp-server"] } } }`}</div>
